



        Thread state - the representation of complete lifecycle of a thread.
                     - threads can exists in six distinct states
                     -NEW - thread created but not yet started
                     -RUNNABLE - thread is ready to run and waiting for CPU scheduler
                     -RUNNING - thread is actually executing code on CPU
                     -BLOCKED - thread is waiting to enter in synchronized block/method
                     -WAITING - thread is waiting indefinitely until another threads signals it
                     -TIMED_WAITING - thread is waiting for limited time (sleep(ms), join(ms), wait(ms))
                     -TERMINATED - thread is finished execution

       flow  - NEW (start())---> RUNNABLE (CPU scheduler picks)---> RUNNING (finished execution) ---> TERMINATED
                                                                  (BLOCKED,WAITING,TIMED_WAITING)- happens
